content.problemStatement:
A **default constructor** in C++ is a special member function that is used to **initialize objects of a class**. It is automatically called when an object of the class is created. Default constructors help in setting up initial values or performing setup operations when the object is formed.
- Must have the same name as the class.
- Does not have a return type (not even void).
- Can be `default` (no parameters) or `parameterized` (with parameters).

**Syntax:** 
```cpp
class ClassName {
public:
    // Default Constructor
    ClassName() {
        // Initialization code
    }
};
```
---
**Example:** 
```cpp
#include 
using namespace std;

class Seedit {
public: // Access Specifier: 'public' means that the members below are accessible from outside the class
    // Default Constructor
    SEED-IT() {
        cout << "Default Constructor is called!" << endl;
    }
};

int main() {
    // Creating an object, which triggers the default constructor
    SEED-IT obj1;  // Default Constructor is called automatically

    return 0;
}
```
**Expected Output:**
```default
Default Constructor is called!
```

